<br>
However, I think that it, along with many another games, cannot really be defined by what it actually is. It's an ever-changing game played by millions of people, sure -- but it's also a world within itself.<br>
<br>
On this server (and I'll use it as an example for obvious reasons), we've crafted a unique economy. We debate what is and isn't acceptable moral and ethical code on our server, and beyond that, what we simply won't allow. It's a tiny, but functional (much like I say about myself when trying to pick up girls <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) society, where we have certain bodies of authority (GMs representing the police, Verant representing the government, guilds being gangs [were we to be compared to an inner-city] or social clubs, the twinked newbie being the rich kid who got his way through college paid by his businessman father, and the common player being your hard-working Joe Schmoe).<br>
<br>
We spend our days embedded in this world (or for those of you with lives, part of your day) or crowded around these boards conversing about being embedded in this world; only some of us realize that we are participating in a model that could be related with our actual civilization. Or maybe I'm just way off-base here, or I've said the obvious, or whatever. I was just thinking about how complex EQ can be at some points, and that led to this rambling, incoherent post. <p>-----<br><img . src="http://www.members.aol.com/aquasol/neosig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A> at: 7/9/02 9:15:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/9/02 11:32:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2272.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I just noticed something</span><hr size=1> Rambling incoherence is a good thing (or so I tell myself as I post something long) ;-)<br>
<br>
Yes this is a community, a slice of &quot;civilisation&quot; for good or ill.  I think that's why I like FV better than the blue, I feel like I am a part of something larger.<br>
<br>
