<br>
I was not an Economics major as an undergrad (heh Electrical Engineering is about the furthest thing from it), but I did enjoy the few Econ classes I had to take.  What really fascinates me is that Everquest is about the closest your ever going to get to a truly free market economics system.  People may say &quot;suchandsuch isnt worth that!&quot; or &quot;Thats way too much,&quot;  but what it really comes down to is that items are worth exactly what they sell for (I know it sounds dumb, but its not always true... look at taxes).  Value is determined on a case by case basis, and the overall average is usually accepted over time.<br>
<br>
Just like a real economic system, money flows into the economy (by killing mobs that drop plat) and it also exits the economy (by buying consumable items such as peridots, etc, from NPC merchants).  I remember on my old server going to EC (that was the big trade zone) with about 5,000pp and walking out an hour later with 10,000pp.  It was great.<br>
<br>
What also has happened is that this &quot;virtual economy&quot; has been linked to our real world economy (hi ebay and playerauctions).  <br>
<br>
<br>
Truly remarkable, if you ask me<br>
